@NODE INTRODUCTION "ScreenShell.guide/Introduction"
                               @{u}@{b}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

    SShell  (or  ScreenShell) is a tool to open a full screen Shell.  It is
designed for those of you who enjoy both working with a nice environment in
a colorfull Workbench, and a clan and fast replying Shell.

    Since  the  developpment  of  OS  2.04  and  3.0, it possible to open a
Workbench  screen with more than 4 colors.  Users with AGA or more machines
can  open  a  256  colors  workbench.   As  it  is a real progress from the
esthetic  point  of  view,  it  can  quickly  become  a  shame  for a Shell
environment  user.  AmigaDos 3.0 has been realy display speed optimised but
the scrolling in a Shell still look like (french Untranslatable) "#@$#$§ of
bitplane display.... bandwith eater.... perhaps CHUNKY...Who know !"...

    So  SShell resolve these problems by displaying on its own full screen.
Window  borders and screen bar supressing allows the use of the all surface
on  the  screen.   For example, a standard screen of NTSC:640x200 and topaz
font size 8 can display 25 lines by 80 characters.

@ENDNODE

